page.title: 13MORESTON FARM HUNDLETON
page.content: Moreston Farm occupies 140 acres. There are 9 cows, 25 suckling calves, 12 fat cattle, 35 two-year-olds and store cattle, 49 ewes, 1 ram,40 lambs, 12 hens, 1 cockerel, 3 ducks, 1 drake, 20 geese, 1 working dog and 3 pet dogs. Four people work on the farm. Their names are Joan Freeman, Anne Freeman and Lesley Mason. Their machinery consists of 3 tractors, 1 trailer, 1 dung-spreader, 1 elevator, 2 ploughs and 1 potato digger. The working dog's name is Taffy. The pet dogs are Melanie, Jasmine and Joshua.
